<br>
Don't play a warrior, they suck for xp compared to sk/paly and always have IMO.  But if you don't have a bard/chanter maybe warrior would be an ok choice.<br>
<br>
Gotta have the cleric IMO.  Unless you want to beg for rezzes.<br>
<br>
My opinion if you want to xp is to provide the base of every xp group:<br>
1) Cleric<br>
2) Enchanter<br>
3) Tank--SK/Paly<br>
Then recruit 3 DPS! to your group.  Next thing you know you'll be 65.  And if you can't find dps, then start killing, there will be people available eventually.<br>
<br>
And yes, I know there are many groupings with less than 6 people that provide good xp.  However, with the xp changes you want to fill your group.  There are an infinite number of combinations that allow good xp to be had.  I've been in many groups without tanks, without healers, etc.  They all work.  But many of them involved getting buffs outside the group to maximize xp production.  Or you have to have a source of rez for the inevitable death.<br>
<br>
Veng Z'Myne--Coercer<br>
